WEBVTT

00:01.736 --> 00:05.270
Each candidate will get
one minute to answer questions

00:05.272 --> 00:07.206
and 30 seconds
for follow-ups and rebuttals.

00:07.208 --> 00:08.841
I'll give candidates time
to respond

00:08.843 --> 00:11.510
if they've been singled out and
criticized by another candidate.

00:11.512 --> 00:13.712
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

00:13.714 --> 00:15.214
All right, candidates.

00:15.216 --> 00:17.216
Let's begin.
[ Applause ]

00:17.218 --> 00:19.118
I didn't say everybody.

00:19.120 --> 00:20.619
Yeah, just the ones
you don't like.

00:20.621 --> 00:21.987
Get rid of everybody,

00:21.989 --> 00:23.856
ain't no one to pick the
cantaloupes and what have you.

00:23.858 --> 00:25.824
We need some of them.
-[ Sighs ]

00:25.826 --> 00:28.460
What we don't need
are the murderers and thugs.

00:28.462 --> 00:29.495
Your plan won't work.

00:29.497 --> 00:30.829
You know how I know
it won't work?

00:30.831 --> 00:32.531
Eisenhower tried the same thing,
sending out a posse

00:32.533 --> 00:34.233
<i> to round up Mexicans</i>
<i> in the '50s.</i>

00:34.235 --> 00:35.901
Ancestry.
Hit the hypocrisy.
<i> Eisenhower didn't have drones.</i>

00:35.903 --> 00:38.070
<i> We have the technology now</i>

00:38.072 --> 00:41.173
to build an electric cyber-wall

00:41.175 --> 00:42.674
from San Diego to Brownsville.
[ Buzzes ]

00:42.676 --> 00:43.675
Time's up.

00:43.677 --> 00:45.477
If I may,
Mr. Doyle should remember

00:45.479 --> 00:47.146
that his own
great-grandfather...

00:47.148 --> 00:48.547
-Senator --
-...emigrated from Ireland

00:48.549 --> 00:50.649
and worked
at tobacco fields illegally.

00:50.651 --> 00:52.051
Time is up.

00:52.053 --> 00:53.852
<i> All right.</i>

00:53.854 --> 00:56.955
<i> Madam Vice President,</i>
<i> anything to add?</i>

00:59.026 --> 01:00.893
Madam Vice President?

01:00.895 --> 01:05.030
It's a big problem.

01:05.032 --> 01:06.131
We need to do better.

01:09.937 --> 01:11.270
<i> All right.</i>

01:11.272 --> 01:12.571
She's having a stroke.

01:12.573 --> 01:14.406
We're watching her
stroke-out on camera.

01:14.408 --> 01:16.708
This is very bad.
<i> The next question is</i>
<i> to Senator Grant.</i>

01:16.710 --> 01:19.178
If you were to lose
the nomination --

01:19.180 --> 01:20.345
Not going to happen.

01:20.347 --> 01:22.548
Humor me, hypothetically,
were you to lose,

01:22.550 --> 01:25.751
who amongst your opponents would
you rather see as president?

01:25.753 --> 01:27.920
She's painting the image
of a losing Mellie.
Mellie:<i> I believe it is high</i>
<i> time that a woman</i>

01:27.922 --> 01:29.755
<i> should run this country,</i>
<i> be commander in chief.</i>
She'll pivot,
use it to attack Hollis.

01:29.757 --> 01:31.623
<i> I am that woman.</i>

01:31.625 --> 01:35.961
Vice President Ross is a decent,
hardworking public servant,

01:35.963 --> 01:38.430
and she would be worlds better
and far more deserving

01:38.432 --> 01:40.732
of this office than the
misogynist playboy to my left.

01:40.734 --> 01:42.734
Playboy?!
Now, hold on a minute.

01:42.736 --> 01:45.537
You flew the entire lineup
of a New Orleans strip club

01:45.539 --> 01:47.606
to your hunting cabin
for the weekend.

01:47.608 --> 01:50.142
I can only imagine what your
plans for Camp David would be.

01:50.144 --> 01:51.910
A lot like
your ex-husband's, I'd expect.

01:51.912 --> 01:54.146
[ Laughter ]

01:54.148 --> 01:56.081
This isn't funny.
I'm sorry.

01:56.083 --> 01:58.550
This man has shipped
over 600,000

01:58.552 --> 02:02.221
American middle-class jobs
to India and China and Mexico,

02:02.223 --> 02:04.590
all just to add a few million
to his stack of...

02:04.592 --> 02:05.657
Billions.
<i> ...billions.</i>

02:05.659 --> 02:07.559
<i> Ole Hollis is</i>

02:07.561 --> 02:11.930
the only one on this stage
ever made a damn thing...

02:11.932 --> 02:14.399
[ Cheers and applause ]
...or done a damn thing,

02:14.401 --> 02:16.935
including firing people
and restructuring

02:16.937 --> 02:19.738
and all the horrible
and necessary things

02:19.740 --> 02:22.007
people in the real world
got to do

02:22.009 --> 02:24.243
to stay alive and competitive.

02:24.245 --> 02:27.346
And, hell yes, I made a buck
or two along the way.

02:27.348 --> 02:29.081
I'm damn proud of that.

02:29.083 --> 02:32.117
Listen, if all it takes
to be presidential

02:32.119 --> 02:35.154
is to shake hands
and give speeches

02:35.156 --> 02:38.757
and know which color lipstick
to wear to the party,

02:38.759 --> 02:40.125
then go ahead on.

02:40.127 --> 02:42.027
Take your pick
of one of these Bettys.

02:42.029 --> 02:43.762
But answer me this, Senator --

02:43.764 --> 02:46.165
how presidential is it

02:46.167 --> 02:49.835
to have your ex-husband's
ex-mistress

02:49.837 --> 02:51.837
running your campaign?

02:51.839 --> 02:53.539
<i> -May I respond?</i>
<i> -Not yet.</i>

02:53.541 --> 02:55.274
<i> That ain't presidential.</i>

02:55.276 --> 02:56.808
It's downright weird.

02:56.810 --> 02:58.443
You want to question
my choices?
And confusing as hell!

02:58.445 --> 03:00.712
Let's talk about the choices
that you have made.

03:00.714 --> 03:03.815
After a quick break,
Senator Grant.

03:03.817 --> 03:08.120
<i> You are watching the first</i>
<i> Republican debate live on BNC.</i>

03:08.122 --> 03:11.156
<i> Stay with us.</i>
<i> We're just getting started.</i>

03:11.158 --> 03:13.592
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

03:17.164 --> 03:18.497
Man: And we're clear.

03:18.499 --> 03:20.799
[ Applause ]

03:20.801 --> 03:25.070
Phew. Hotter than two squirrels
screwing in a wool sock.

03:26.907 --> 03:28.207
I missed my shot
at ancestry.

03:28.209 --> 03:29.374
-You're doing great.
-I could have led with it.

03:29.376 --> 03:30.909
I'll drive the point home
in the spin room.

03:30.911 --> 03:32.044
But don't worry about it.

03:32.046 --> 03:33.478
You need to respond
to what he said

03:33.480 --> 03:34.580
about us working together.

03:34.582 --> 03:36.014
Yes, sir.
I've got her. Hold.

03:36.016 --> 03:38.517
Susan, I have the president
on the line.

03:38.519 --> 03:40.052
Hello?

03:40.054 --> 03:42.154
Susan, having fun?

03:42.156 --> 03:44.523
Fun? No, sir.

03:44.525 --> 03:46.658
You lost a few rounds.
It doesn't matter. Shake it off.

03:46.660 --> 03:48.193
Tomorrow,
no one will be talking

03:48.195 --> 03:49.928
about who stumbled here
or fumbled there.

03:49.930 --> 03:51.330
They'll only talk about
who won.

03:51.332 --> 03:53.398
That will be you.

03:53.400 --> 03:55.400
You only need one moment,
one punch.

03:55.402 --> 03:58.503
-20 seconds.
-One good one is all it takes.

03:58.505 --> 04:00.105
[ Applause ]

04:00.107 --> 04:03.609
Man: 3...2...

04:03.611 --> 04:05.777
Welcome back.

04:05.779 --> 04:07.713
My next question
is about gun control,

04:07.715 --> 04:09.581
and it's for you,
Senator Grant.

04:09.583 --> 04:12.351
<i> According to</i>
<i> a recent BNC poll...</i>
How is she doing?

04:12.353 --> 04:13.585
Ow.

04:13.587 --> 04:15.354
We're in real trouble here
because of you.

04:15.356 --> 04:17.389
Couldn't you have
at least waited until tomorrow

04:17.391 --> 04:18.357
to break her heart?

04:18.359 --> 04:19.691
She figured it out
on her own.

04:19.693 --> 04:21.560
When you walk out
on that stage with her,

04:21.562 --> 04:23.729
everybody better be smiling,
David, because if they're not,

04:23.731 --> 04:26.465
I swear to God
I will end you.

04:26.467 --> 04:28.634
<i> What are your feelings</i>
<i> on the matter, Senator Grant?</i>

04:28.636 --> 04:30.102
My views on gun control --

04:30.104 --> 04:32.137
I yield to no one in my support
of the second amendment.

04:32.139 --> 04:33.438
Oh, please.

04:33.440 --> 04:36.041
This woman's husband
stood behind that same podium

04:36.043 --> 04:39.411
less than three years ago,
made the same empty promises.

04:39.413 --> 04:41.647
Then, once he's re-elected --
boom! --

04:41.649 --> 04:45.384
comes out strong in favor
of tighter gun restrictions.

04:45.386 --> 04:47.619
How do we know this Grant
ain't the same as the other one?

04:47.621 --> 04:49.087
Come on, Mellie.

04:49.089 --> 04:52.424
Because this is
the 21st Century.

04:52.426 --> 04:54.893
<i>You can't look at a man anymore</i>
<i> and assume that his wife</i>

04:54.895 --> 04:56.828
<i> shares the same positions,</i>

04:56.830 --> 04:59.598
nor can you hold the wife
accountable for his actions.

04:59.600 --> 05:02.100
We are not our husbands'
keepers, as they say.

05:02.102 --> 05:03.735
We are our own women,

05:03.737 --> 05:04.936
<i> with our own beliefs.</i>

05:04.938 --> 05:06.672
<i> And in case there is</i>
<i> any doubt</i>

05:06.674 --> 05:09.107
<i> about where I stand</i>
<i> on the president,</i>

05:09.109 --> 05:10.942
you'll notice
he's my ex-husband,

05:10.944 --> 05:11.910
not my husband.

05:11.912 --> 05:14.112
[<i> Applause</i> ]

05:14.114 --> 05:15.747
It is a good line.

05:15.749 --> 05:18.483
Sally:<i> Madam Vice President,</i>
<i> you've been awfully quiet.</i>

05:18.485 --> 05:20.285
<i> Do you agree with Mrs. Grant's</i>

05:20.287 --> 05:23.488
assessment that women are not
their husbands' keepers,

05:23.490 --> 05:26.858
or do you think
she should be held accountable

05:26.860 --> 05:28.660
for her husband's decisions?

05:29.630 --> 05:31.430
Come on, Susan,
seize the moment.

05:31.432 --> 05:34.099
<i> No.</i>

05:34.101 --> 05:35.434
<i> We are not</i>
<i> our husbands' keepers.</i>

05:37.104 --> 05:39.538
That's it?

05:39.540 --> 05:40.972
Mr. Doyle --

05:40.974 --> 05:42.641
But maybe we should be.

05:42.643 --> 05:43.909
I'm sorry?

05:44.712 --> 05:46.311
What is she doing?

05:46.313 --> 05:48.280
Here we go.

05:48.282 --> 05:51.817
<i> My husband, John,</i>
<i> served in the U.S. Army.</i>

05:51.819 --> 05:52.884
<i> He was a lieutenant</i>

05:52.886 --> 05:55.787
in the 116th Infantry Brigade,

05:55.789 --> 05:58.790
served all over the world,
including Afghanistan,

05:58.792 --> 06:01.727
where his platoon was tasked
with the rather onerous job

06:01.729 --> 06:04.629
of patrolling
a 20-mile stretch of desert

06:04.631 --> 06:06.398
along the Kandahar-Herat
highway.

06:06.400 --> 06:08.367
He called me one night
while he was over there,

06:08.369 --> 06:10.669
and when he told me
what their assignment was,

06:10.671 --> 06:11.970
I said, "Well, what is it

06:11.972 --> 06:13.905
about this 20-mile
stretch of desert

06:13.907 --> 06:15.841
that's so important
to our country?

06:15.843 --> 06:18.543
Is it a village that needs
protecting from the Taliban,

06:18.545 --> 06:21.513
a prison where
we're holding terrorists?"

06:21.515 --> 06:23.348
"No," he says.

06:23.350 --> 06:25.584
"It's a pipeline."

06:25.586 --> 06:28.253
a pipeline
that the Afghani government,

06:28.255 --> 06:30.922
in exchange
for billions of dollars,

06:30.924 --> 06:34.526
was allowing American companies
to build on its land.

06:34.528 --> 06:37.396
One of those companies --
Doyle Energy.

06:37.398 --> 06:39.030
[ Laughs ] Okay.
This --

06:39.032 --> 06:41.600
I'm talking now.

06:41.602 --> 06:47.572
<i> Hearing my husband say that,</i>
<i> it made my blood boil.</i>

06:47.574 --> 06:49.708
<i> Here he was,</i>

06:49.710 --> 06:51.276
putting his life at risk

06:51.278 --> 06:54.513
so American businessmen
could line their pockets.

06:54.515 --> 06:57.449
I wanted to say something,
voice my rage,

06:57.451 --> 06:59.618
tell my husband
to get the hell out of there,

06:59.620 --> 07:02.521
but I didn't.

07:02.523 --> 07:06.425
I bit my tongue, because we are
not our husbands' keepers.

07:09.029 --> 07:11.263
14 hours later, a Taliban sniper

07:11.265 --> 07:13.698
put a bullet
through my husband's neck,

07:13.700 --> 07:17.436
severed his carotid artery,
killed him almost instantly.

07:17.438 --> 07:20.038
<i> I didn't blame the shooter.</i>

07:20.040 --> 07:22.741
<i> I didn't even blame</i>
<i> the government</i>

07:22.743 --> 07:24.643
or the energy companies.

07:24.645 --> 07:26.211
I blamed myself.

07:26.213 --> 07:29.648
I had an opinion,
and I didn't voice it.

07:29.650 --> 07:33.585
I kept my mouth shut,
and I swore that day

07:33.587 --> 07:36.087
that I would never again
be silent.

07:36.089 --> 07:38.223
I became
a United States senator,

07:38.225 --> 07:41.426
I became the Vice president
of the United States of America,

07:41.428 --> 07:44.429
and I plan to become the
president of the United States,

07:44.431 --> 07:47.265
because no, we are not
our husbands' keepers,

07:47.267 --> 07:49.067
but maybe
we should be America's.

07:53.607 --> 07:54.639
Next question.

07:54.641 --> 07:57.843
[ Cheers and applause ]

08:00.581 --> 08:04.649
Oh, please. If we can hold
the applause, please.

08:04.651 --> 08:07.252
[ Cheers and applause continue ]

08:07.254 --> 08:09.588
She did it.

08:09.590 --> 08:12.424
♪♪

08:17.097 --> 08:21.132
Sally: Liberty lovers, the first
Republican debate is over,

08:21.134 --> 08:24.169
and Susan Ross
was the clear winner.

08:24.171 --> 08:26.538
And to her, I say bravo.

08:26.540 --> 08:28.673
It's clear that Susan
is the kind of strong,

08:28.675 --> 08:31.476
moral woman America is looking
for to be their president.

08:31.478 --> 08:34.012
One would hope Mellie Grant
would have the good sense

08:34.014 --> 08:35.881
to drop out early
and let Vice President Ross

08:35.883 --> 08:37.516
collect the female vote.

08:37.518 --> 08:38.350
But will she?

08:40.454 --> 08:43.889
Mellie, it was one debate,
one loss -- one loss.

08:43.891 --> 08:45.557
A hard one I know,

08:45.559 --> 08:47.225
but you can't take it
personally.

08:47.227 --> 08:51.329
Olivia...

08:51.331 --> 08:54.366
America hates me.

08:54.368 --> 08:57.569
They hate who I am,
where I've been,

08:57.571 --> 09:01.373
who I think I have the audacity
to try to become.

09:01.375 --> 09:03.074
That's personal.

09:04.044 --> 09:06.411
They hate me.

09:11.251 --> 09:12.484
And they love Susan.

09:12.486 --> 09:14.819
Hey, we will win this.

09:14.821 --> 09:16.621
[ Sighs ]
You keep saying that.

09:21.662 --> 09:23.395
Look at me.

09:27.167 --> 09:29.401
Mellie,
I will get you in the Oval,

09:29.403 --> 09:31.570
come Hell or high water.

09:34.107 --> 09:36.541
[ Sighs ]

09:36.543 --> 09:39.444
♪♪

09:42.783 --> 09:45.383
I hate to admit it,
but Susan Ross won
that fair and square.

09:45.385 --> 09:46.851
Hard to compete
with a dead husband.

09:46.853 --> 09:48.186
We won't have to.

09:48.188 --> 09:50.922
-Why not?
-Because he's not her husband.

09:50.924 --> 09:53.625
Susan Ross is a liar.

09:53.627 --> 09:55.393
We're gonna find out why,

09:55.395 --> 09:57.095
and then we're gonna
take her down.

10:03.070 --> 10:04.703
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

10:04.705 --> 10:06.805
Why the heck would they choose
a picture of David and me

10:06.807 --> 10:08.440
when I'm the one
who won the debate?!

10:08.442 --> 10:10.141
Well, America doesn't care
about you winning a debate.

10:10.143 --> 10:11.309
You won David.

10:11.311 --> 10:13.612
My phone's been ringing
off the hook all morning.

10:13.614 --> 10:15.413
Every publication
in this country

10:15.415 --> 10:17.782
wants an exclusive about
your relationship with David --

10:17.784 --> 10:19.451
<i> The Journal, Vanity Fair.</i>

10:19.453 --> 10:21.486
<i> The Emerald,</i>
your high-school paper, called.

10:21.488 --> 10:22.721
[ Knock at door ]

10:23.924 --> 10:25.657
-Hi.
-What's he doing here?

10:25.659 --> 10:26.491
I asked him to come by.

10:26.493 --> 10:28.293
Elizabeth --

10:28.295 --> 10:29.828
I have a round of interviews
with local affiliates lined up

10:29.830 --> 10:31.930
for the two of you together.

10:31.932 --> 10:33.832
You need to sell
this love story.

10:33.834 --> 10:35.166
It's critical.

10:35.168 --> 10:37.802
I will do whatever Susan
needs me to do.

10:37.804 --> 10:40.405
I want her to be president.
I owe her that.

10:40.407 --> 10:43.241
♪♪

10:48.448 --> 10:51.416
No.
Why does it have to be me?

10:51.418 --> 10:53.318
You're smart, even-keeled,
good with people.

10:53.320 --> 10:54.619
She's not people.

10:54.621 --> 10:57.355
She is a privileged,
miserable, mean --

10:57.357 --> 10:59.524
Marcus --
Look, she can go
with someone else.

10:59.526 --> 11:01.760
You will be on the road
with a presidential candidate.

11:01.762 --> 11:02.927
That's brass ring, Marcus.

11:02.929 --> 11:05.463
For anyone but me.

11:05.465 --> 11:06.765
I'm too dangerous.

11:06.767 --> 11:07.966
Huck stays here.

11:07.968 --> 11:09.100
Well, what about Quinn?

11:09.102 --> 11:10.969
I need Quinn here
to help on Susan Ross.

11:10.971 --> 11:12.504
So you need Quinn and you need
Huck, but you don't need me?

11:14.174 --> 11:16.141
What I need is for you

11:16.143 --> 11:18.176
to get Mellie on a plane
and fly to Los Angeles

11:18.178 --> 11:20.145
so she can be likable to America
on "Jimmy Kimmel."

11:20.147 --> 11:22.113
I need you to do your job.

11:24.051 --> 11:26.217
Whatever.

11:33.560 --> 11:35.927
Ready to go get them,
Mellie?

11:37.064 --> 11:38.329
My bag is over there.

11:38.331 --> 11:41.032
[ Sam & Dave's
"Hold On, I'm Comin'" plays ]

11:44.638 --> 11:47.372
Lieutenant John Latner,
killed by a Taliban sniper

11:47.374 --> 11:49.507
outside of Kandahar
on a routine patrol.

11:49.509 --> 11:50.875
What's their story?

11:50.877 --> 11:52.510
John and Susan lived
on the same block growing up.

11:52.512 --> 11:54.479
On-again, off-again
through high school.

11:54.481 --> 11:56.514
Susan's on record
in several news publications

11:56.516 --> 11:58.583
saying she and John
went to the justice of the peace

11:58.585 --> 12:00.652
on a whim just before
his first deployment in 2006.

12:00.654 --> 12:02.187
And?

12:02.189 --> 12:04.389
♪ And about to drown ♪

12:04.391 --> 12:06.091
♪ Hold on ♪
County clerk's office
is old-school paper.

12:06.093 --> 12:07.559
Took me all night,
but it's not there.

12:07.561 --> 12:09.394
♪ I'm comin' ♪
No marriage certificate on file.

12:09.396 --> 12:10.995
♪ Hold on ♪
I checked January and March
to be safe.

12:10.997 --> 12:12.497
So she's lying.
Let's go to the press.

12:12.499 --> 12:13.932
-No.
-No?

12:13.934 --> 12:15.066
If the press calls Susan out
for lying about being married,

12:15.068 --> 12:16.735
she'll just spin it,
say she lied in order

12:16.737 --> 12:18.570
to protect her daughter.
Easy.

12:18.572 --> 12:20.505
But if she lied in order
to collect veteran's benefits

12:20.507 --> 12:22.173
she was never actually
entitled to --

12:22.175 --> 12:23.775
Then she's not just a liar,
she's a thief,

12:23.777 --> 12:24.843
unfit to be president.

12:24.845 --> 12:26.344
That's unspinnable.
That's...cold.

12:26.346 --> 12:27.545
That's politics.

12:27.547 --> 12:29.748
John's beneficiary information
isn't digitized.

12:29.750 --> 12:31.916
I can't exactly pick
the front lock of the Pentagon.

12:31.918 --> 12:33.785
♪ Hold on ♪
Susan's bank statements.

12:33.787 --> 12:35.920
♪ I'm comin' ♪

12:35.922 --> 12:38.356
♪ Hold on ♪

12:38.358 --> 12:40.024
♪ I'm comin' ♪

12:40.026 --> 12:41.693
♪ Hold on ♪

12:41.695 --> 12:43.261
Nothing.

12:43.263 --> 12:45.396
No regular deposits from
the Army into Susan's accounts.

12:45.398 --> 12:46.531
Check again.

12:46.533 --> 12:48.199
Maybe Susan is
just a good person who lied

12:48.201 --> 12:49.634
to protect her kid.

12:49.636 --> 12:51.569
Quinn: Whoo!

12:51.571 --> 12:54.239
Okay, Susan definitely
didn't receive any money

12:54.241 --> 12:56.207
from the government,
but I followed up

12:56.209 --> 12:58.376
on a suspicious check in 2007
to an Aston Labs.

12:58.378 --> 13:00.211
It's a DNA testing facility.

13:00.213 --> 13:02.947
Susan paid for a DNA test
for Casey.

13:02.949 --> 13:04.582
Not only
was she never married to John --

13:04.584 --> 13:06.918
John isn't Casey's father.

13:06.920 --> 13:08.753
♪ Hold on ♪
So who is?

13:08.755 --> 13:10.955
♪ I'm comin' ♪
And why is Susan
hiding him?

13:10.957 --> 13:13.424
♪ Hold on ♪

13:13.426 --> 13:14.492
♪ I'm comin' ♪

13:14.494 --> 13:15.794
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

13:17.230 --> 13:19.164
Olivia:
You're holding out on me.

13:19.166 --> 13:21.299
-I'm not sure what you mean.
-Susan Ross.

13:21.301 --> 13:23.802
Oh. Yeah, I was wondering why
she was still standing.

13:23.804 --> 13:24.936
You know what I want.

13:24.938 --> 13:26.571
You want me to say
I knew John Latner

13:26.573 --> 13:28.239
wasn't her baby daddy,
and you want my source

13:28.241 --> 13:30.074
so you can track down
Casey's biological father.

13:30.076 --> 13:31.609
You can't knock me
for trying to squirrel

13:31.611 --> 13:33.178
a little something away
for winter.

13:33.180 --> 13:34.612
I've got a general election
to win.

13:34.614 --> 13:36.080
You won't make it
to the general

13:36.082 --> 13:36.815
unless you use
what I gave you on Edison.

13:36.817 --> 13:38.149
Amazing.

13:38.151 --> 13:40.185
We're in a mutually beneficial
situation again.

13:40.187 --> 13:41.753
I gave you
what I had on Edison.

13:41.755 --> 13:43.121
No, you gave me a rumor.

13:43.123 --> 13:44.589
It's a rumor
because I can't find

13:44.591 --> 13:45.623
a second source
to verify it.

13:45.625 --> 13:48.026
That's a shame.

13:48.028 --> 13:49.494
Is this
how you usually negotiate?

13:49.496 --> 13:52.063
Because you kind of suck.

13:53.934 --> 13:55.266
Leslie Tannen.

13:55.268 --> 13:56.367
She was
the admitting nurse

13:56.369 --> 13:57.468
at Meridian Terrace
during that time.

13:57.470 --> 13:58.703
She'll confirm.

13:58.705 --> 14:00.205
Your turn. Susan Ross.

14:00.207 --> 14:01.940
Who's the real father?
Is he around?

14:01.942 --> 14:04.709
Mm. Oh, yeah.

14:04.711 --> 14:06.611
He's not going anywhere.

14:06.613 --> 14:08.246
[ Buzzes ]

14:11.184 --> 14:13.284
[ Buzzes ]

14:16.156 --> 14:18.223
Who the hell are you?

14:20.160 --> 14:21.326
I'm here to talk to you

14:21.328 --> 14:23.027
about your relationship
with Susan Ross.

14:27.234 --> 14:28.433
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

14:30.370 --> 14:31.469
Meridian Terrace --

14:31.471 --> 14:33.538
a rehab facility
in West Virginia.

14:33.540 --> 14:36.574
Edison went there eight years
ago after he had a car accident.

14:36.576 --> 14:38.509
Showed up at the place
with some achy bones

14:38.511 --> 14:40.211
and a vicious addiction
to painkillers.

14:40.213 --> 14:42.146
Went back a year later
for depression.

14:42.148 --> 14:43.514
That's a personal matter.
Out of bounds.

14:43.516 --> 14:46.017
I'm glad that Senator Davis
got the help he needed.

14:46.019 --> 14:47.685
[ Sighs ]
This is how we do it every time.

14:47.687 --> 14:49.053
I tell you
what mud to sling.

14:49.055 --> 14:50.421
You play church boy
to start,

14:50.423 --> 14:52.156
and eventually,
you come around to my side.

14:52.158 --> 14:53.358
Look, America has
a right to know

14:53.360 --> 14:54.726
if a candidate's
a pill-popper.

14:54.728 --> 14:55.860
Tell him I'm right,
old-school.

14:55.862 --> 14:57.161
It's risky.

14:57.163 --> 14:58.496
People with
mental-health problems

14:58.498 --> 15:00.565
aren't stigmatized
like they used to be.

15:00.567 --> 15:02.567
But those people
don't have the nuclear codes

15:02.569 --> 15:03.534
at their fingertips.

15:03.536 --> 15:05.169
Even so,
I don't comment on rumors.

15:05.171 --> 15:06.170
Now,
I got a speech to prep.

15:11.211 --> 15:15.380
Your hand is dangerously close
to the flame.

15:15.382 --> 15:17.115
Watch out, kid.

15:22.222 --> 15:24.088
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

15:24.090 --> 15:26.357
Senator Grant,
so nice to meet you.

15:26.359 --> 15:27.225
Big fan.

15:27.227 --> 15:29.294
Well, that is always nice
to hear.

15:29.296 --> 15:31.062
So, what we'd love is for you
to read some mean tweets.

15:31.064 --> 15:33.631
Mean tweets?

15:33.633 --> 15:35.400
You read mean things people say
about you on Twitter.

15:35.402 --> 15:37.368
Oh.
It's funny.
People love it.

15:37.370 --> 15:39.103
So, for example,
"Mellie Grant looks

15:39.105 --> 15:40.138
just like
my girlfriend's dog.

15:40.140 --> 15:42.273
I hate that dog."
Stuff like that.

15:42.275 --> 15:44.709
I would read that out loud?
That was --

15:44.711 --> 15:45.543
Not mean enough.

15:45.545 --> 15:46.978
What?

15:46.980 --> 15:48.313
Can you find meaner tweets
than these?

15:48.315 --> 15:50.214
Uh, yeah.
How mean do you want them?

15:50.216 --> 15:51.883
Mean.

15:51.885 --> 15:54.385
Your wish is my command.
Nice to meet you, Senator.

15:54.387 --> 15:56.087
Hmm.

15:56.089 --> 15:58.122
This was a terrible idea.

15:59.659 --> 16:02.060
Terrible!

16:04.164 --> 16:06.497
Me and Susan -- we knew each
other all through growing up.

16:06.499 --> 16:08.599
Our daddies worked
in the mines together.

16:08.601 --> 16:12.837
And, then, uh, in high school,
we -- we became sweethearts.

16:12.839 --> 16:14.105
[ Chuckles ]

16:14.107 --> 16:16.808
She was --
She was always real smart.

16:16.810 --> 16:18.343
How's she doing?

16:18.345 --> 16:20.979
Did she tell you
that Casey is your daughter?

16:20.981 --> 16:23.781
No.
And why would she say that?

16:23.783 --> 16:26.484
I think you had an affair with
Susan while she was with John.

16:26.486 --> 16:29.187
You don't know that.

16:30.690 --> 16:33.024
I know a lot of highly placed
people in Washington

16:33.026 --> 16:35.259
and people
who already think

16:35.261 --> 16:37.762
our country's drug laws
are too strict.

16:37.764 --> 16:38.997
We could get you out.

16:41.434 --> 16:43.468
And what would you want
from me for that?

16:43.470 --> 16:44.702
Just the truth, Ronnie.

16:44.704 --> 16:46.537
You'd submit
to a paternity test,

16:46.539 --> 16:49.674
then make a public statement
saying that Casey is your child.

16:49.676 --> 16:52.477
But if I did that,
then people would think

16:52.479 --> 16:55.279
she was hiding something,
and here I am in prison.

16:55.281 --> 16:56.481
[ Chuckles ]

16:56.483 --> 16:59.183
Now, I-I don't think
that'd be very good for Susan.

16:59.185 --> 17:01.319
I mean,
she's trying to be president.

17:01.321 --> 17:03.721
You've been in this place
for 10 years.

17:03.723 --> 17:07.592
You help me and by this time
next week, you'll be a free man.

17:12.232 --> 17:14.766
I don't know.
I got to think about it.

17:16.069 --> 17:17.402
Don't take too long.

17:20.974 --> 17:23.207
[ Buzzes ]

17:24.811 --> 17:26.377
You sure
you want to do this?

17:26.379 --> 17:28.746
Even if he talks,
who's gonna believe a felon?

17:28.748 --> 17:29.981
They'll believe
a paternity test.

17:29.983 --> 17:31.215
I read Ronnie's file.

17:31.217 --> 17:32.817
They gave him the chance
to testify

17:32.819 --> 17:34.085
against his dealer friends

17:34.087 --> 17:35.686
in return
for a reduced sentence.

17:35.688 --> 17:37.188
He's not a snitch.

17:37.190 --> 17:39.157
Well, maybe 10 years in prison
has softened his resolve.

17:43.063 --> 17:45.163
[ Buzzes ]

17:46.766 --> 17:49.200
What was that about?

17:49.202 --> 17:51.169
Susan lied and then decided
to run for president.

17:51.171 --> 17:52.570
She's asking for it.

17:52.572 --> 17:53.871
Casey is just a kid.

17:53.873 --> 17:55.506
This isn't politics.

17:55.508 --> 17:58.076
This is ripping a family apart
for no reason.

17:58.078 --> 18:02.046
It's a presidential campaign,
Huck,

18:02.048 --> 18:03.548
and we're losing.

18:03.550 --> 18:05.083
You know
how much she hates to lose.

18:06.686 --> 18:08.252
It could be worse.

18:08.254 --> 18:10.855
We could be
making stuff up.

18:10.857 --> 18:12.290
[ Pounds on door ]

18:16.229 --> 18:18.830
[ Knock at door ]

18:22.602 --> 18:23.601
Don't sit.

18:23.603 --> 18:26.037
[ Sighs ] Can we talk?

18:26.039 --> 18:27.905
I don't care
what Elizabeth thinks.

18:27.907 --> 18:29.307
We shouldn't
be doing this.

18:29.309 --> 18:31.642
Tell me something I don't know,
stupid face.

18:31.644 --> 18:33.811
We should just
put out a statement that says

18:33.813 --> 18:36.214
we really care for each other
and that we tried,

18:36.216 --> 18:40.618
but we both should be focusing
on working for the country,

18:40.620 --> 18:41.819
and we remain close friends

18:41.821 --> 18:43.754
and wish each other well,
that kind of thing.

18:43.756 --> 18:46.124
People will hear that.
People will understand.

18:46.126 --> 18:50.161
You know what people will
understand when they hear that?

18:50.163 --> 18:52.597
That the person in
the relationship with a penis --

18:52.599 --> 18:54.632
that's you --
cheated on the person

18:54.634 --> 18:56.834
in the relationship
without one -- that's me --

18:56.836 --> 18:59.103
and that we are looking
for a way out

18:59.105 --> 19:00.972
that doesn't make me
look bad.

19:00.974 --> 19:03.441
I don't want to fake it
anymore either,

19:03.443 --> 19:05.676
but there is no version
of us breaking up

19:05.678 --> 19:08.613
that looks good for me,
unless you're willing to say

19:08.615 --> 19:11.315
that I left you because
you're an impotent alcoholic

19:11.317 --> 19:13.851
who hates kids and dogs
and God.

19:13.853 --> 19:15.353
Are you willing to say that?

19:16.990 --> 19:19.157
Yes, I will say that.

19:19.159 --> 19:21.592
I will say
whatever you want me to say.

19:21.594 --> 19:23.661
But what I want to say to you,
Susan,

19:23.663 --> 19:25.830
is that I love you.

19:25.832 --> 19:27.498
I want to say that,

19:27.500 --> 19:29.333
and that I hope that
you'll consider forgiving me

19:29.335 --> 19:30.868
and that that you'll let me
earn your trust back

19:30.870 --> 19:33.638
and that we won't have to
break up or fake it,

19:33.640 --> 19:37.208
because we'll just be us
together.

19:37.210 --> 19:39.911
So, that's what
I'd like to say.

19:46.219 --> 19:49.520
♪♪

19:50.957 --> 19:52.323
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

19:52.325 --> 19:54.492
Shocking allegations
coming to light this hour

19:54.494 --> 19:56.060
regarding
Democratic presidential hopeful

19:56.062 --> 19:57.528
Edison Davis.

19:57.530 --> 19:59.897
The senator reportedly
checking himself into

19:59.899 --> 20:02.466
a West Virginian rehab facility
eight years ago

20:02.468 --> 20:04.569
after struggling with,
and I quote,

20:04.571 --> 20:06.904
"a vicious addiction
to painkillers."

20:06.906 --> 20:09.941
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

20:18.384 --> 20:20.751
[ Sighs ]

20:22.255 --> 20:24.088
You shouldn't
have leaked this.
It's gonna be fine.

20:24.090 --> 20:26.057
Alex talked to the director
of Meridian Terrace.

20:26.059 --> 20:27.658
She was the head nurse
at the same time

20:27.660 --> 20:28.993
that Edison Davis
was there.

20:28.995 --> 20:30.228
She confirmed everything.

20:30.230 --> 20:32.763
We make this kind of allegation
and we get it wrong,

20:32.765 --> 20:35.600
we could take a hit in the polls
that we'd never recover from.

20:35.602 --> 20:38.569
My brother ran both my campaigns
as governor.

20:38.571 --> 20:40.905
Never once has he sent me down
the wrong path.

20:45.945 --> 20:48.479
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:49.749 --> 20:51.215
-Governor --
-Governor Vargas --

20:51.217 --> 20:52.850
Governor,
who do you think won

20:52.852 --> 20:53.751
the Republican debate
last night?

20:53.753 --> 20:55.186
Big money
and the big banks.

20:55.188 --> 20:56.621
Certainly not
the American people.

20:56.623 --> 20:58.789
<i> The Philadelphia Courier</i>
is saying that Edison Davis

20:58.791 --> 21:01.792
was in rehab for addiction
to painkillers and depression.

21:01.794 --> 21:02.860
Care to comment?

21:02.862 --> 21:04.095
I've seen the reports,

21:04.097 --> 21:05.296
and I'm glad
he sought treatment.

21:05.298 --> 21:07.031
Should it disqualify him
from being president?

21:09.802 --> 21:11.902
That's not for me to say.

21:11.904 --> 21:13.070
<i> I do know that generally,</i>

21:13.072 --> 21:14.605
<i> these things</i>
<i> are a lifelong struggle,</i>

21:14.607 --> 21:17.108
<i> and the job of president</i>
<i> is already hard enough,</i>

21:17.110 --> 21:18.909
<i> but I hope that he keeps</i>
<i>getting the help that he needs.</i>

21:18.911 --> 21:21.045
I can't believe this.

21:21.047 --> 21:23.714
-You assured me this was buried.
-It was.

21:23.716 --> 21:25.249
Then how did this --

21:25.251 --> 21:27.718
Your daughter. That's how.

21:27.720 --> 21:30.655
She was the only person
who knew.

21:30.657 --> 21:33.724
You need to go to her
and pull back the reins

21:33.726 --> 21:34.959
and stop her in her tracks

21:34.961 --> 21:36.627
before she gets any more
out of control.

21:36.629 --> 21:38.162
Did you hear me?!

21:38.164 --> 21:39.630
Olivia did this!

21:39.632 --> 21:42.867
♪♪

21:47.140 --> 21:48.639
I can't quite decide
which part

21:48.641 --> 21:51.275
of your indecorous behavior
troubles me more,

21:51.277 --> 21:53.978
the decision to interrupt me
while I was speaking,

21:53.980 --> 21:57.915
the distasteful reference
to my daughter requiring reins,

21:57.917 --> 22:02.320
or this foolish belief that I
would ever take orders from you!

22:02.322 --> 22:03.521
-Eli --
-Oh, you want to be a boss?

22:03.523 --> 22:04.588
Is that it?

22:04.590 --> 22:05.823
No. I-I --

22:05.825 --> 22:07.425
Spit it out, son!

22:07.427 --> 22:09.293
Speak with some spirit!

22:09.295 --> 22:11.996
Do you want to be a boss?!

22:11.998 --> 22:13.297
No, sir.

22:13.299 --> 22:16.033
So you don't want to be
president?

22:16.035 --> 22:19.170
-Of course I --
-Then you want to be a boss!

22:19.172 --> 22:22.707
Which is it, yes or no?!

22:27.313 --> 22:30.014
Should you ever

22:30.016 --> 22:33.384
be so unwise as to forget
who the real boss,

22:33.386 --> 22:37.221
the only boss, is
around here again,

22:37.223 --> 22:39.490
Meridian Terrance?

22:39.492 --> 22:42.026
[ Chuckles ]

22:42.028 --> 22:44.962
That will be
the last of your worries.

22:47.066 --> 22:49.433
I can guarantee that.

22:51.804 --> 22:53.571
I'll handle this my way.

22:53.573 --> 22:56.307
Until then, I suggest
that you keep out of my sight

22:56.309 --> 23:00.711
and keep my daughter's name
out of your mouth.

23:00.713 --> 23:04.148
♪♪

23:10.056 --> 23:11.389
If you're hungry,

23:11.391 --> 23:12.723
there's more chicken
in the fridge.

23:21.667 --> 23:23.100
You guys,
I think you'll want to see this.

23:28.040 --> 23:30.841
Woman:
<i> I'm not sure how that rumor</i>
<i> got started, but it's a lie.</i>

23:30.843 --> 23:33.511
<i> As a former nurse and now</i>
<i> director of this facility,</i>

23:33.513 --> 23:36.013
<i> I can say</i>
<i> that Senator Edison Davis</i>

23:36.015 --> 23:37.214
<i> did not receive treatment</i>

23:37.216 --> 23:39.250
for addiction
at Meridian Terrace.

23:39.252 --> 23:40.551
Reporter:<i> Are you saying</i>
<i> Frankie Vargas is lying?</i>

23:40.553 --> 23:42.586
You told me
your source was solid.
She was.

23:42.588 --> 23:43.721
Leslie:<i> I'm -- I'm saying</i>
<i> the whole thing is ridiculous.</i>

23:43.723 --> 23:46.190
<i> Governor Vargas' decision</i>
<i> to comment</i>

23:46.192 --> 23:49.627
<i> on unsubstantiated rumors</i>
<i> is hurtful</i>

23:49.629 --> 23:52.630
<i> and totally uncalled for,</i>
<i> and I-I'm --</i>

23:52.632 --> 23:56.934
<i> I'm sorry Senator Davis</i>
<i>and his family have had to deal</i>

23:56.936 --> 24:01.939
<i> with allegations</i>
<i> that have zero basis in fact.</i>

24:01.941 --> 24:04.375
<i> No one --</i>
<i> No one deserves that.</i>

24:04.377 --> 24:06.210
Reporter:
<i> Do you even know the senator?</i>

24:08.614 --> 24:09.647
You screwed me.

24:09.649 --> 24:11.081
What are you talking about?

24:11.083 --> 24:13.217
According to Leslie Tannen,
Edison never set foot

24:13.219 --> 24:14.852
on the grounds
of Meridian Terrace.

24:15.922 --> 24:17.588
Someone got to her.

24:17.590 --> 24:19.723
Or you lied to get what you
wanted to take down Susan Ross.

24:19.725 --> 24:21.459
Don't put this on me.

24:21.461 --> 24:22.793
If someone got Leslie
to agree to a cover-up,

24:22.795 --> 24:24.061
if they had the time
to bribe her,

24:24.063 --> 24:25.429
to threaten her
into changing her tune,

24:25.431 --> 24:26.797
then you're the one
who did move quick enough.

24:26.799 --> 24:28.165
[ Chuckles lightly ]

24:28.167 --> 24:30.434
I hope to hell you can
get that charmless robot

24:30.436 --> 24:31.936
of yours nominated,
because that will give me

24:31.938 --> 24:34.038
a chance to wipe the floor
with you in November.

24:36.676 --> 24:39.243
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

24:39.245 --> 24:41.011
You'll be reading the tweets
off a cellphone.

24:41.013 --> 24:42.746
"Mean tweets."
"Mean" doesn't even cover it.

24:42.748 --> 24:44.248
Crude, vile,
disgusting tweets, maybe.

24:44.250 --> 24:46.250
I should be talking about
real issues,

24:46.252 --> 24:48.519
real things,
expounding real views.
Senator --

24:48.521 --> 24:50.855
After all, I just debated
my ass off on national TV.

24:50.857 --> 24:52.623
Senator, please.
And now I'm gonna
make a fool of myself

24:52.625 --> 24:54.024
doing some stupid
comedy bit.

24:54.026 --> 24:56.660
Are you kidding me with
how annoying you are right now?!

24:56.662 --> 24:58.762
I mean, damn!

24:59.599 --> 25:01.332
Excuse me?

25:01.334 --> 25:04.368
You are relentless
with your whining

25:04.370 --> 25:05.970
and your groaning
and your complaining.

25:05.972 --> 25:07.705
You are officially
the worst!

25:07.707 --> 25:10.941
You have no idea
what I am going through,

25:10.943 --> 25:12.877
what I have been through,

25:12.879 --> 25:14.278
the kinds of things
that people are saying about me.

25:14.280 --> 25:16.013
This is exactly why people
don't like you.

25:16.015 --> 25:17.314
This is exactly
why<i> I</i> don't like you,

25:17.316 --> 25:19.149
even though
I'm being paid to like you.

25:19.151 --> 25:21.452
This is exactly
why you'll never be president.

25:28.494 --> 25:31.128
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

25:31.130 --> 25:34.131
♪♪

25:49.749 --> 25:51.315
Time's up, Ronnie.

25:51.317 --> 25:53.350
We need to take your blood now
for the paternity test.

25:53.352 --> 25:55.419
Now, look, uh, Miss Pope.

25:55.421 --> 25:57.655
I prayed on it
for a real long time,

25:57.657 --> 25:59.723
and, uh...

25:59.725 --> 26:02.826
I-I just can't do it.

26:02.828 --> 26:05.896
I can't ruin the lives
of the people I care about.

26:05.898 --> 26:08.365
I just can't do it.

26:08.367 --> 26:11.068
This is your chance
to leave this place,

26:11.070 --> 26:12.670
to get out of here
for good.

26:12.672 --> 26:15.372
<i> This</i> is your chance,
and you are wasting it!

26:15.374 --> 26:16.907
Look, when Susan
becomes president next year,

26:16.909 --> 26:18.075
she's gonna help me
get out of here.

26:18.077 --> 26:19.109
[ Laughs ]

26:19.111 --> 26:20.044
Yeah.

26:20.046 --> 26:21.612
And you --
you may be special

26:21.614 --> 26:23.180
with your fancy contacts
and all,

26:23.182 --> 26:24.348
but you ain't more special

26:24.350 --> 26:25.849
than the president
of the United States.

26:25.851 --> 26:27.418
Do you honestly think the
president of the United States

26:27.420 --> 26:29.086
will have anything
to do with you, Ronnie?!

26:29.088 --> 26:31.889
You are protecting someone
who doesn't even remember you.

26:31.891 --> 26:32.957
I don't believe that.

26:32.959 --> 26:34.258
She squashed you like a bug
11 years ago,

26:34.260 --> 26:35.759
and she never looked back.

26:35.761 --> 26:37.795
She doesn't think about you.
She doesn't visit you.

26:37.797 --> 26:38.629
She doesn't care about you.

26:38.631 --> 26:39.964
Yes, she does.

26:39.966 --> 26:40.965
Do you want to stay here
another decade!

26:40.967 --> 26:42.433
With good behavior,

26:42.435 --> 26:43.801
I'll be out of this place
in three more years.

26:43.803 --> 26:45.269
Not when some prison guard

26:45.271 --> 26:47.471
finds a little oxy
underneath your mattress.

26:47.473 --> 26:50.040
That's another four years
for hiding contraband.

26:50.042 --> 26:51.642
What?
I don't have any --
Add another five

26:51.644 --> 26:52.710
for the marijuana
you've been smuggling

26:52.712 --> 26:53.811
through the visitation room.

26:53.813 --> 26:55.279
How easy would it be
to plant anything we want

26:55.281 --> 26:57.615
in Ronnie's bunk, Quinn?

27:03.489 --> 27:05.055
Quinn!

27:06.892 --> 27:08.225
We've done it before.

27:08.227 --> 27:09.560
I don't see
how we couldn't do it again.

27:09.562 --> 27:12.830
♪♪

27:18.471 --> 27:20.104
You wouldn't.

27:20.106 --> 27:25.409
You have no idea
what I'm capable of.

27:31.651 --> 27:34.418
Now, do we have a deal?

27:34.420 --> 27:37.321
♪♪

27:49.168 --> 27:51.135
Ronnie Miller's paternity test.
He's definitely the dad.

27:51.137 --> 27:53.103
That good enough for you?
-Not just good. That's great.

27:53.105 --> 27:55.673
Leak this to the media --
TV, print, online.

27:55.675 --> 27:56.840
I want to see Ronnie's face.

27:56.842 --> 27:58.375
I want to hear Ronnie's name
everywhere.

27:58.377 --> 28:00.277
Good work, people.

28:00.279 --> 28:03.013
You mind taking BNC?
I really don't like those dudes.

28:04.517 --> 28:06.383
Huck.

28:06.385 --> 28:07.818
I'm not taking BNC,
and neither are you.

28:07.820 --> 28:09.386
-What?
-This is wrong, Quinn.

28:09.388 --> 28:11.221
We can't do this.
-No, but Liv just said --

28:11.223 --> 28:13.190
I don't care what Liv just said.
She wants us to play dirty

28:13.192 --> 28:14.792
because her candidate
lost a debate.

28:14.794 --> 28:16.460
She wants to destroy
a little girl's life

28:16.462 --> 28:18.195
because her candidate is down
in a few polls.

28:18.197 --> 28:19.463
We can't do this.

28:19.465 --> 28:21.365
No, she wants to do
what's best for her client.

28:21.367 --> 28:22.499
You're taking it personal.

28:22.501 --> 28:25.202
It is personal!
She's crossing a line.

28:25.204 --> 28:26.503
She's going somewhere
she'll never be able

28:26.505 --> 28:27.337
to find her way back from.

28:27.339 --> 28:29.540
We can't do this.

28:31.644 --> 28:33.711
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

28:36.015 --> 28:37.414
[ Sighs ]
This had better be good.

28:37.416 --> 28:39.249
I'm sorry, it's not enough
that I actually bring coffee.

28:39.251 --> 28:40.984
You're pre-complaining
about the quality?

28:40.986 --> 28:42.586
I'm talking about
the photos.
What photos?

28:42.588 --> 28:44.188
You said in your text
you have compromising photos

28:44.190 --> 28:45.389
of the treasury secretary.

28:45.391 --> 28:48.092
Oh, right, that.
No, I want to talk about Liv.

28:48.094 --> 28:49.927
Wait. You lied to me?
Yes.

28:49.929 --> 28:52.396
So, you're saying there are
no photos of Secretary Foster?

28:52.398 --> 28:53.831
Who?

28:53.833 --> 28:55.933
[ Sighs ]
What's going on with Liv?

28:55.935 --> 28:58.202
She's crossing the line,
Abby.

28:58.204 --> 29:00.270
What line?
Whatever one
is in front of her.

29:00.272 --> 29:01.371
-Is this about the election?
-Yes.

29:01.373 --> 29:02.873
It's an election.
It's rough and tumble.

29:02.875 --> 29:04.508
It's brutal. You know this.
-It's not like that.

29:04.510 --> 29:05.909
Besides,
you shouldn't be talking

29:05.911 --> 29:07.411
about this with me anyway,
because we're not exactly

29:07.413 --> 29:08.612
on the same side
of things here.

29:08.614 --> 29:10.547
We're on the same side
of our friend, aren't we?

29:10.549 --> 29:14.351
I'm not talking about a tough
campaign, hardball tactics.

29:14.353 --> 29:16.553
I am talking about our friend
crossing the line.

29:16.555 --> 29:18.722
I am talking about
replacing the white hat

29:18.724 --> 29:20.424
with a black skullcap.

29:20.426 --> 29:23.393
You know the kind of thing
I'm talking about?

29:23.395 --> 29:26.296
♪♪

29:41.280 --> 29:42.980
[ Chuckles ]

29:48.287 --> 29:50.654
[ Sighs ]

29:54.994 --> 29:56.593
I should have called.
I know.

29:56.595 --> 29:58.395
Fitz.
What are you doing here?

29:58.397 --> 29:59.630
Giving you some advice.

29:59.632 --> 30:00.931
Some advice?

30:00.933 --> 30:02.499
That's what we do now,
right?

30:02.501 --> 30:05.135
Drop by each other's offices,

30:05.137 --> 30:07.504
exchange a few pleasantries,
and give each other some advice,

30:07.506 --> 30:10.107
even when the other person
never asked for it.

30:10.109 --> 30:12.309
I haven't been able to think
of something pithy enough

30:12.311 --> 30:14.178
to say, like,
"The fish rots from the head,"

30:14.180 --> 30:18.448
but I thought
we're keeping it real

30:18.450 --> 30:21.118
with each other now,
so...

30:21.120 --> 30:22.920
Can I keep it real
with you, Liv?

30:26.258 --> 30:29.893
Whoever taught you that phrase
should be fired immediately.

30:32.464 --> 30:35.499
Go ahead. Keep it real.

30:37.636 --> 30:41.505
Ronnie Miller's DNA test.

30:41.507 --> 30:42.806
How'd you get it?

30:42.808 --> 30:45.275
That's your only concern
right now -- how I got it?

30:45.277 --> 30:47.277
-It was supposed --
-It doesn't matter, Liv.

30:47.279 --> 30:50.614
What matters is that you're back
to your same, old dirty tricks.

30:50.616 --> 30:53.116
How are you not sick
of playing this game?

30:53.118 --> 30:54.985
Oh, I am the one
playing a game?

30:54.987 --> 30:56.386
Right. Of course.

30:56.388 --> 30:58.455
Because it's not like you
showed up here

30:58.457 --> 31:01.758
with your charming smile
and your cute, little sayings,

31:01.760 --> 31:03.894
pretending to give me
some advice,

31:03.896 --> 31:06.997
trying to shame me into
not using the very information

31:06.999 --> 31:08.532
that will sink your candidate
or anything.

31:08.534 --> 31:11.368
You're so above playing games,
aren't you, Fitz?

31:11.370 --> 31:13.537
I suppose if there were ever
a manipulation going on,

31:13.539 --> 31:15.172
you'd be the first
to recognize it.

31:15.174 --> 31:16.573
The only reason
why you are here

31:16.575 --> 31:18.342
is because this affects your
candidate.

31:18.344 --> 31:20.043
I am here because
I believe in my candidate

31:20.045 --> 31:21.578
because my candidate is
brilliant

31:21.580 --> 31:23.247
and passionate
and inspiring --

31:23.249 --> 31:25.048
And a liar!

31:25.050 --> 31:27.751
She lied to the public.
She lied to you.

31:27.753 --> 31:29.319
And your candidate's
so different?

31:29.321 --> 31:32.689
I happen to think that Mellie
will be a great president.

31:32.691 --> 31:36.326
She is smart, hardworking.
She cares about this country.

31:36.328 --> 31:37.995
You married her, Fitz,
had children with her.

31:37.997 --> 31:39.263
You must have thought
the same thing

31:39.265 --> 31:40.530
about her at some point.

31:40.532 --> 31:42.733
What can I say?
You think you know a person.

31:42.735 --> 31:44.668
Funny how that works.

31:46.071 --> 31:47.738
[ Sighs ]

31:47.740 --> 31:49.740
I am trying to change, Liv.

31:49.742 --> 31:52.910
I am trying
to be the better person.
Right.

31:52.912 --> 31:55.345
I don't want what happened to me
to happen to Susan!

31:55.347 --> 31:58.382
I don't want her to win
by deceit!

31:58.384 --> 32:01.118
I don't want her to be
the victim of another Defiance!

32:01.120 --> 32:04.855
Is that what you think
you were -- a victim?

32:04.857 --> 32:06.590
Please!

32:06.592 --> 32:07.724
You know damn well

32:07.726 --> 32:10.093
that receiving stolen property
is a crime.

32:10.095 --> 32:11.929
You got exactly
what you wanted!

32:11.931 --> 32:14.231
You think I wanted to win
that way?!

32:14.233 --> 32:16.400
You think anyone did?!

32:16.402 --> 32:19.636
♪♪

32:26.712 --> 32:30.113
If you don't have anything
else to say,

32:30.115 --> 32:33.550
any more advice to give --

32:33.552 --> 32:36.586
We have the chance
to do things differently now,

32:36.588 --> 32:38.588
not only for them,
but for us.

32:38.590 --> 32:42.159
This is our chance
to move forward,

32:42.161 --> 32:46.063
to run a campaign
in a hard-fought,

32:46.065 --> 32:48.865
competitive,
and honorable way.

32:51.170 --> 32:53.170
We're not these people
anymore, Liv.

32:53.172 --> 32:56.673
We don't have to be
these people anymore.

32:59.812 --> 33:03.080
♪♪

33:30.642 --> 33:31.942
Olivia's going to help him
tell the world

33:31.944 --> 33:34.111
that Casey's his child?
Yes.

33:36.482 --> 33:37.814
This is a nightmare.

33:37.816 --> 33:39.282
I can make this go away,
Susan.

33:39.284 --> 33:41.051
I can commute his sentence.

33:41.053 --> 33:42.352
We can strike a deal.

33:42.354 --> 33:45.288
From what I understand,
he doesn't want to talk,

33:45.290 --> 33:47.157
and we can ensure
that he won't.

33:47.159 --> 33:49.526
I can make this go away.

33:49.528 --> 33:51.895
Okay, then. Thank you.

33:51.897 --> 33:52.929
Is that
what you want to do?

33:53.565 --> 33:55.232
Yes!

33:55.234 --> 33:57.534
Of course.
What choice do I have?

33:57.536 --> 33:59.569
You could come clean.

33:59.571 --> 34:01.304
I can't do that.

34:01.306 --> 34:02.873
The man
who fathered my child

34:02.875 --> 34:05.075
isn't the man who I pretended
to be married to,

34:05.077 --> 34:07.344
but is another man
who is actually in prison?

34:07.346 --> 34:09.513
That's not going to
go over very well.

34:09.515 --> 34:11.581
I agree.

34:11.583 --> 34:13.350
But the truth might.

34:13.352 --> 34:15.652
You were in a loving,
long-term relationship

34:15.654 --> 34:17.821
with a man who served proudly
and capably

34:17.823 --> 34:21.158
in the United States
military.

34:21.160 --> 34:24.361
Shortly into that relationship,
you made a mistake --

34:24.363 --> 34:27.864
a mistake that gave you
a beautiful baby girl

34:27.866 --> 34:31.334
who was subsequently raised
in a loving family

34:31.336 --> 34:32.836
with a loving mother
and father.

34:32.838 --> 34:35.939
You are imperfect.

34:35.941 --> 34:38.108
You are human.
You made a mistake.

34:38.110 --> 34:40.444
And you have owned up
to that mistake

34:40.446 --> 34:43.447
and asked for the forgiveness
of the American people.

34:43.449 --> 34:46.249
Will they accept this
and continue to support you?

34:46.251 --> 34:50.087
I don't know.
But I think that they might.

34:51.590 --> 34:52.923
I know I will.

34:54.893 --> 34:56.426
I can't do that
to Casey.

34:56.428 --> 34:57.861
[ Chuckles ]

34:57.863 --> 35:01.198
Far be it from me
to tell you how to parent.

35:02.701 --> 35:04.134
But I know you.

35:04.136 --> 35:06.570
If you decide not
to go public with this,

35:06.572 --> 35:09.206
it won't be because
you're protecting Casey.

35:09.208 --> 35:10.540
Don't fool yourself.

35:10.542 --> 35:12.976
It will only be because
you're protecting the path

35:12.978 --> 35:15.045
to this office
because you believe it is worth

35:15.047 --> 35:17.280
whatever it takes
to get here.

35:20.786 --> 35:22.652
Let me tell you, Susan,

35:22.654 --> 35:25.989
that is not true.

35:27.726 --> 35:30.293
I don't think you understand,
Mr. President.

35:30.295 --> 35:32.462
If this comes out,
I'll be ruined.

35:32.464 --> 35:34.564
This will destroy me.

35:34.566 --> 35:35.732
No.

35:35.734 --> 35:37.834
What will destroy you
is if you take this office

35:37.836 --> 35:39.970
and you didn't earn it.

35:39.972 --> 35:41.671
I did not earn this office.

35:48.947 --> 35:52.048
I was not fairly elected
to this office.

35:55.187 --> 35:56.853
I did not earn it.

35:56.855 --> 35:59.189
Sir?

36:03.996 --> 36:06.496
I am going to tell you
a story,

36:06.498 --> 36:10.934
and you are gonna tell me
who you want to be,

36:10.936 --> 36:15.338
and I hope who you want to be
is better than me.

36:20.145 --> 36:21.678
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

36:21.680 --> 36:25.048
[ Door opens ]

36:25.050 --> 36:27.083
[ Sighs ]
What do you want?

36:29.288 --> 36:31.054
[ Sighs ]

36:31.623 --> 36:33.190
I'm doing the show, Marcus.
What?

36:33.192 --> 36:35.625
"Is that bougie-ass scarf
cutting the air off

36:35.627 --> 36:39.596
to Marcus Walker's brain,
or is he just plain dumb?"

36:41.166 --> 36:42.532
[ Sighs ]

36:42.534 --> 36:44.067
[ Chuckles ]

36:44.069 --> 36:46.570
"More flavor in a dry saltine
than Marcus Walker.

36:46.572 --> 36:50.540
Can we say Boresville?"

36:50.542 --> 36:55.979
"Those mutton chops, though?
You ain't Shaft, bro. #SMH."

36:55.981 --> 36:57.480
It means shaking my head.

36:57.482 --> 36:58.915
Okay.

36:58.917 --> 37:01.418
It's what they tweeted about me
when I ran for mayor.

37:01.420 --> 37:03.520
Guess what trended
48 hours after I announced.

37:03.522 --> 37:05.021
Go ahead.
I have no idea.

37:05.023 --> 37:06.456
My high booty.

37:07.025 --> 37:08.658
Your what?

37:08.660 --> 37:10.227
Apparently, I have
what the twitterverse refers to

37:10.229 --> 37:11.828
as a "high booty."

37:11.830 --> 37:13.997
I wear my pants too high,

37:13.999 --> 37:17.000
belt too tight just to --
you know?

37:17.002 --> 37:18.568
[ Chuckling ]
Show off your high booty?

37:18.570 --> 37:19.569
That right there.

37:19.571 --> 37:20.704
[ Chuckles ]

37:20.706 --> 37:22.572
That's the person
they need to see --

37:22.574 --> 37:25.408
someone relaxed,
someone who can laugh --

37:25.410 --> 37:26.543
laugh at herself.

37:26.545 --> 37:27.510
[ Sighs ]

37:27.512 --> 37:29.212
You're scared to lose.

37:29.214 --> 37:32.682
Trust me,
I know the feeling.

37:32.684 --> 37:35.018
But you have a chance
right now to show the world

37:35.020 --> 37:37.187
there's another side
of Senator Mellie Grant,

37:37.189 --> 37:40.190
a side that America
can fall in love with.

37:40.192 --> 37:42.559
Do not waste it.

37:42.561 --> 37:44.427
Use it.

37:44.429 --> 37:47.163
Use it and win.

37:50.636 --> 37:52.435
[<i> Camera shutter clicking</i> ]

37:52.437 --> 37:55.505
♪♪

38:12.891 --> 38:15.058
Sir, I've made a decision.

38:16.061 --> 38:17.127
I have some difficult news,
Susan.

38:19.331 --> 38:20.664
Have a seat.

38:27.806 --> 38:29.572
I want Ronnie to wear that suit
for the interview,

38:29.574 --> 38:30.907
okay, those shoes.

38:30.909 --> 38:33.410
What time
are you going to the jail?

38:34.646 --> 38:36.413
Quinn, what?

38:38.150 --> 38:40.984
Ronnie's dead, Liv.

38:40.986 --> 38:42.819
He hanged himself
in his cell.

38:42.821 --> 38:46.189
♪♪

38:49.661 --> 38:51.695
Frankie, got that list
of field directors you wanted.

38:51.697 --> 38:53.596
You want to take a quick look
before I start contacting folks?

38:53.598 --> 38:56.032
Why don't you hand that
over to Cyrus?

38:56.034 --> 38:57.701
I thought
Alex was handling it.

38:57.703 --> 39:00.337
He was,
and now he's not.

39:03.342 --> 39:04.774
Alex, hand the list over
to Cyrus.

39:04.776 --> 39:07.077
He'll take over from there.

39:08.347 --> 39:10.547
Alex, give my campaign manager
the paper.

39:10.549 --> 39:12.649
Yeah.

39:12.651 --> 39:14.384
Okay. Understood.

39:18.790 --> 39:20.724
Mr. Beene.

39:20.726 --> 39:22.926
Ah. My ride is here.

39:24.329 --> 39:27.697
We'll get back at it...

39:27.699 --> 39:29.799
bright and early.

39:29.801 --> 39:31.835
♪ Sunny ♪

39:31.837 --> 39:33.370
Nice work
on Meridian Terrace.

39:33.372 --> 39:35.405
It's like Edison Davis
was never there.

39:35.407 --> 39:36.740
That was the job, sir.

39:36.742 --> 39:38.408
And a job well-done.
Thank you, Tom.

39:38.410 --> 39:39.909
My pleasure, sir.

39:39.911 --> 39:41.544
<i> People are obsessed</i>
<i> with you two.</i>

39:41.546 --> 39:43.713
-We've heard.
<i> -Why do you think that is?</i>

39:43.715 --> 39:44.981
I think it's simple,
Trish.

39:44.983 --> 39:46.683
America loves a love story.

39:46.685 --> 39:49.753
Frankly, so do I.

39:49.755 --> 39:51.588
<i> Very good,</i>
<i> Madam Vice President.</i>

39:51.590 --> 39:53.857
<i> Thank you both so much</i>
<i> for joining us today.</i>

39:53.859 --> 39:55.859
-Thank you.
-Our pleasure.

39:55.861 --> 39:57.827
Feed's down.
Tallahassee's in 10 minutes.

39:57.829 --> 39:59.028
Keep up the energy, people.

39:59.030 --> 40:00.663
You're doing great,
you know?

40:00.665 --> 40:02.832
-Mm-hmm.
-I'm happy I could be of help,

40:02.834 --> 40:04.667
even happier
that you've forgiven me.

40:04.669 --> 40:07.003
You're a prop, David.
That's all.

40:08.874 --> 40:14.544
♪ Thank you
for the sunshine bouquet ♪

40:14.546 --> 40:16.246
♪ Sunny ♪

40:16.248 --> 40:18.248
I need your help.

40:18.250 --> 40:19.249
♪ Thank you for the... ♪
[ Cheers and applause ]

40:19.251 --> 40:21.050
So, as you know,
from time to time,

40:21.052 --> 40:23.052
we give famous people
a chance to read

40:23.054 --> 40:24.254
some of the horrible things

40:24.256 --> 40:26.356
people say about them
on Twitter.

40:26.358 --> 40:28.725
And today,
we extended the opportunity

40:28.727 --> 40:31.361
to our former first lady
and current candidate

40:31.363 --> 40:33.596
for president,
Senator Mellie Grant.

40:33.598 --> 40:36.466
And to all of our surprise,
she said yes.

40:36.468 --> 40:39.002
[ Cheers and applause ]

40:48.380 --> 40:50.413
[ Laughter ]

40:50.415 --> 40:52.315
[ Cheers and applause ]

41:02.160 --> 41:04.894
[ Cheers and applause ]

41:04.896 --> 41:08.832
♪ Thank you for the truth
